s. (sa. teertha.) ceremonial purity
சுத்தம்
2. sacred rivers
or waters at a place of pilgrimage
or as brought from such place
புண்ணியதீர்த்தம்
3. consecrated water used for washing an idol
which is afterward brought out and given to the people
especially on the last day of the festival
either to be drunk by them
or taken home for the sick to dispel diseases
திருமஞ்சனநீர்
